"> </span><span class=\"bp\">+</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">⨅</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">i</span><span class=\"o\">,</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">f</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">i</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">⨅</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">i</span><span class=\"o\">,</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"mi\">1</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">+</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">f</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">i</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"k\">by</span>\n<span class=\"w\">  </span><span class=\"n\">rw</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">[</span><span class=\"n\">add_ciInf</span><span class=\"o\">]</span>\n<span class=\"w\">  </span><span class=\"n\">exact</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">Finite</span><span class=\"bp\">.</span><span class=\"n\">bddBelow_range</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">_</span>\n</code></pre></div>\n<p>We already have the lemma to do this in ints (and AddGroup in general) but it looks like we were missing it for nat-like things</p>",
