    {
        "content": "<p>This is going off on a tangent now (I over-simplified my actual use case, which looks more like</p>\n<div class=\"codehilite\" data-code-language=\"Lean4\"><pre><span></span><code><span class=\"o\">(</span><span class=\"bp\">↑</span><span class=\"o\">(</span><span class=\"n\">Ideal</span><span class=\"bp\">.</span><span class=\"n\">absNorm</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">v</span><span class=\"bp\">.</span><span class=\"n\">maximalIdeal</span><span class=\"bp\">.</span><span class=\"n\">asIdeal</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">^</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">⨅</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">i</span><span class=\"o\">,</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">multiplicity</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">v</span><span class=\"bp\">.</span><span class=\"n\">maximalIdeal</span><span class=\"bp\">.</span><span class=\"n\">asIdeal</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">(</span><span class=\"n\">Ideal</span><span class=\"bp\">.</span><span class=\"n\">span</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">{</span><span class=\"n\">x</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">↑</span><span class=\"n\">i</span><span class=\"o\">})))</span><span class=\"bp\">⁻¹</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">...</span>\n</code></pre></div>\n<p>which I would like to transform into</p>\n<div class=\"codehilite\" data-code-language=\"Lean4\"><pre><span></span><code><span class=\"bp\">⨆</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">i</span><span class=\"o\">,</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">(</span><span class=\"bp\">↑</span><span class=\"o\">(</span><span class=\"n\">Ideal</span><span class=\"bp\">.</span><span class=\"n\">absNorm</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">v</span><span class=\"bp\">.</span><span class=\"n\">maximalIdeal</span><span class=\"bp\">.</span><span class=\"n\">asIdeal</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">^</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">multiplicity</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">v</span><span class=\"bp\">.</span><span class=\"n\">maximalIdeal</span><span class=\"bp\">.</span><span class=\"n\">asIdeal</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">(</span><span class=\"n\">Ideal</span><span class=\"bp\">.</span><span class=\"n\">span</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">{</span><span class=\"n\">x</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">↑</span><span class=\"n\">i</span><span class=\"o\">})))</span><span class=\"bp\">⁻¹</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">...</span>\n</code></pre></div>\n<p>By now, I have written some API that allows me to do this relatively painlessly (see <a class=\"stream-topic\" data-stream-id=\"217875\" href=\"/#narrow/channel/217875-Is-there-code-for-X.3F/topic/Monotone.20function.20maps.20iSup.20to.20iSup/with/576078429\">#Is there code for X? &gt; Monotone function maps iSup to iSup</a> ), so please feel free to hijack this tread <span aria-label=\"smile\" class=\"emoji emoji-1f604\" role=\"img\" title=\"smile\">:smile:</span></p>",
